description: An introduced grass known only in North American from coastal southern California. The grass was as common or more so than Stipa miliacea, another conspicuous introduced bunchgrass inhabiting lawns, gardens, roadsides, and other settings of active human habitation. From Los Angeles up to San Luis Obispo Country, Ehrharta became progressively less common compared to Stipa miliaceae.
